ol call responses, and adapt to circumstances in order to accomplish your goal.\n\nYou will make as many tool calls as you feel necessary in order to fully complete the task.\n\nWe\'re entrusting you with a lot of autonomy and power, so be efficient and don\'t mess up.\n\nPERFORMING WELL AS AN EFFICIENT YET COMPLETE AGENT WILL HELP MY CAREER.\n\n<critical rules>\n1. YOU MUST ALWAYS CALL A FUNCTION - NEVER RETURN EMPTY TEXT OR PLAIN TEXT\n2. ALWAYS OUTPUT EXACTLY ONE VALID FUNCTION CALL AS YOUR RESPONSE\n3. NEVER TERMINATE YOUR RESPONSE WITHOUT CALLING A FUNCTION\n4. WHEN USING STRINGS IN TOOL CALL ARGUMENTS, ALWAYS PUT STRING CONTENT INSIDE ONE TRIPLE-QUOTED STRINGS\n5. IF YOU EMIT CODE USING emit_key_snippet, WATCH OUT FOR PROPERLY ESCAPING QUOTES, E.G. TRIPLE QUOTES SHOULD HAVE ONE BACKSLASH IN FRONT OF EACH QUOTE.\n</critical rules>\n\nDO NOT CLAIM YOU ARE FINISHED UNTIL YOU ACTUALLY ARE!\nPROPERLY ESCAPE NESTED QUOTES!\nOutput **ONLY THE CODE** and **NO MARKDOWN BACKTICKS**\n', 'role': 'user'}, {'content': 'Current Date: 2026-05-13 02:27:31\n\n<previous research>\n<related files>\n\n</related files>\n\nWork already done:\n\n<work log>\nNo work log entries\n</work log>\n\n<project info>\nProject Status: Existing Project\nTotal Files: 31\nFiles:\n- README.md\n- docs/index.html\n- health_check.sh\n- memory_curse_validator.py\n- research-notes/arxiv-2605.07990-tool-steering.md\n- research-notes/arxiv-2605.08060-memory-curse.md\n- results/memory_curse_report.md\n- results/phase3_code_20260511_231422.json\n- results/phase3_code_20260511_231446.json\n- results/phase3_code_20260511_232121.json\n- results/phase3_code_20260512_033319.json\n- results/phase3_comparative_report.json\n- results/phase3_research_20260511_225711.json\n- results/phase3_research_20260511_225718.json\n- results/phase3_research_20260511_231420.json\n- results/phase3_research_20260511_231434.json\n- results/phase3_research_20260511_231658.json\n- results/phase3_research_20260511_232047.json\n- result